\par You conjure a quasi-real motorcycle. The motorcycle can be ridden only by you or the one person for whom
 you specifically create the cycle. A phantom chopper looks like a heavily customized motorcycle of indeterminate make and model. It has realistic-looking license plates, and you decide what the license plate says when you cast the spell.
\par The }{\i\fs20\cf0 phantom chopper }{\fs20\cf0 has a Defense of 10, hardness of 5, and 20 hit points +1 hit point per caster level. If it loses all its hit points, the }{\i\fs20\cf0 phantom chopper }{\fs20\cf0 disappears. A }{\i\fs20\cf0 phantom chopper }{
\fs20\cf0 has a top speed of 40 feet per caster level, an initiative modifier of +0, and a maneuver modifier of +1.
\par The }{\i\fs20\cf0 phantom choppers }{\fs20\cf0 gains certain powers according to caster level. A motorcycle\rquote s abilities include those of motorcycles of lower caster levels.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 7th Level: }{\fs20\cf0 The motorcycle can ride over sandy, muddy, or even swampy ground without difficulty or decrease in speed.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 8th Level: }{\fs20\cf0 The motorcycle can ride over water as if it were firm, dry ground.
\par }{\i\fs20\cf0 9th Level: }{\fs20\cf0 The motorcycle can ride in the air as if it were firm land, so chasms and the like can be crossed without benefit of a bridge. The }{\i\fs20\cf0 phantom chopper }{\fs20\cf0 
